Appendix C: Detailed Proof of Ostrowski’s Theorem

Theorem C.1 (DeepSeek–Ostrowski Local Convergence Theorem – full details).
Let R: Q_I \to Q_I be Fréchet differentiable at a fixed point q^* with \rho(DR(q^*)) < 1. Then there exists an open ball B(q^*, r) such that for any q_0 \in B(q^*, r), the iteration q_{k+1}=R(q_k) converges to q^*. Moreover, the convergence is Q-linear with rate \kappa = \rho(DR(q^*)): there exists C>0 such that \|q_k - q^*\| \le C \kappa^k \|q_0 - q^*\| for all k.

Proof.
Step 1 – Construct a contractive norm. By Lemma A.8, choose \varepsilon > 0 such that \rho(DR(q^*)) + \varepsilon < 1. Let \kappa = \rho(DR(q^*)) + \varepsilon. There exists an equivalent norm \|\cdot\|_* on Q_I such that \|DR(q^*)\|_* \le \kappa.

Step 2 – Local contraction estimate. Since R is differentiable, for any \eta > 0 there exists r > 0 such that for all q with \|q - q^*\|_* < r,

\|R(q) - R(q^*) - DR(q^*)(q-q^*)\|_* \le \eta \|q - q^*\|_*.

Using R(q^*) = q^* and the triangle inequality,

\|R(q) - q^*\|_* \le \|DR(q^*)(q-q^*)\|_* + \eta \|q - q^*\|_* \le (\|DR(q^*)\|_* + \eta)\|q - q^*\|_*.

Choose \eta small enough that \|DR(q^*)\|_* + \eta \le \kappa. Then for all q in the ball of radius r,

\|R(q) - q^*\|_* \le \kappa \|q - q^*\|_*.

Thus R maps the ball into itself (since \kappa < 1, \|R(q)-q^*\|_* \le \kappa r < r).

Step 3 – Convergence. By induction, for any q_0 in the ball,

\|q_k - q^*\|_* \le \kappa^k \|q_0 - q^*\|_*.

Since \kappa < 1, \|q_k - q^*\|_* \to 0. Because the norm \|\cdot\|_* is equivalent to the original metric d_I, the convergence is also in the original metric with a constant factor: \|q_k - q^*\| \le C \kappa^k \|q_0 - q^*\| for some C>0. ∎

Remark on Q‑linear convergence. The constant C accounts for the norm equivalence. In practice, if one uses the natural norm on the quotient space, the convergence is exactly \kappa-linear after a finite number of steps (since the derivative’s norm can be made arbitrarily close to \rho).

